text: Voom HD Networks was a suite of 25 original high-definition television channels. It was owned by AMC Networks. As part of a 15-year agreement between AMC Networks and Dish Network. They were originally part of the Voom DTH satellite platform launched by Cablevision and were operated by its subsidiary, Rainbow DBS Company.
